    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>onion marmalade </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 1-2 min or until all the liquid has evaporated – this is your <strong>caramelised onion</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>caramelised onion </strong>to a plate then set aside until serving, reserve the pan</p><p>Combine your<strong> mayo</strong> and <strong>truffle olive oil</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>truffle mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657624260035-x200.jpg",
